  const {
    prop1 = 'default 1',
    prop2 = 'default 2',
    prop3 = 'default 3',
  } = object;

  return { prop1, prop2, prop3 };
}
```

2. Using the nullish coalescing operator (`??`)

Defaults will be applied if the properties on `object` are absent, set to `undefined`, or set to `null`.

```javascript
